<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1729" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1729">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 419.11D29/53.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Price</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 28, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Vigorous action continued in the Cocoa Grove matter. Pursuant to your
                            telegram of April 20, Panaman Minister for Foreign Affairs on Saturday
                            promised formal reply to-day advising at least that judge in charge of
                            case would render decision at once and the same would be reviewed by
                            Supreme Court promptly and their decree given within 15 days. Reply not
                            received to-day. Reference to testimony made by Panaman Minister for
                            Foreign Affairs foreshadows, I believe, a judicial whitewashing. I shall
                            make another demand in the morning.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>